">Disclaimers</a></li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<ul id=\"footer-icons\" class=\"noprint\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<li id=\"footer-poweredbyico\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"//www.mediawiki.org/\"><img src=\"/resources/assets/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png\" alt=\"Powered by MediaWiki\" srcset=\"/resources/assets/poweredby_mediawiki_132x47.png 1.5x, /resources/assets/poweredby_mediawiki_176x62.png 2x\" width=\"88\" height=\"31\"/></a>\t\t\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div style=\"clear: both;\"></div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgPageParseReport\":{\"limitreport\":{\"cputime\":\"0.019\",\"walltime\":\"0.037\",\"ppvisitednodes\":{\"value\":133,\"limit\":1000000},\"ppgeneratednodes\":{\"value\":728,\"limit\":1000000},\"postexpandincludesize\":{\"value\":2531,\"limit\":2097152},\"templateargumentsize\":{\"value\":301,\"limit\":2097152},\"expansiondepth\":{\"value\":8,\"limit\":40},\"expensivefunctioncount\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":100},\"unstrip-depth\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":20},\"unstrip-size\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":5000000},\"timingprofile\":[\"100.00%   16.705      1 -total\",\" 48.64%    8.126      1 Template:Variant-343\",\" 37.73%    6.303      2 Template:Scroll\",\" 23.97%    4.004      1 Template:Version_icon\",\" 16.31%    2.725      2 Template:White\",\" 14.06%    2.349      1 Template:Top_icon\",\" 11.72%    1.958      1 Template:Stub\"]},\"cachereport\":{\"timestamp\":\"20240926190303\",\"ttl\":604800,\"transientcontent\":false}}});mw.config.set({\"wgBackendResponseTime\":114});});</script>\n\t</body>\n</html>\n","rawPage":"{{scroll\n |name=detect magic\n |cost=100\n |ink=7-13\n}}\n{{scroll\n |name=magic detection\n |cost=300\n |ink=8-15\n}}\n\nA '''scroll of magic detection''' is a type of [[scroll]] that appears in [[GruntHack]], [[EvilHack]] and [[Hack'EM]]. In GruntHack, it is known as a '''scroll of detect magic''' and has a base cost of 100[[zm]], while in EvilHack and Hack'EM the scroll has a base cost of 300zm.\n\n==Description==\nWhen read, the scroll detects all [[magical item]]s on the current level similar to a [[potion of object detection]], including items with [[object properties]], as well as revealing the current location of [[monster]]s that are capable of casting [[monster spell]]s. The exact effects of the scroll depend on its [[beatitude]]: An uncursed scroll of detect magic will flag all revealed items as \"magical\", while a [[blessed]] scroll will identify the item type and object properties of any detected magical items; a cursed scrolls will also detect [[mimic]]s and wakes up any monsters that it detects.\n{{stub}}\n{{variant-343}}<!--{{variant-36X}}-->\n[[Category:GruntHack scrolls|Detect magic]]\n[[Category:EvilHack scrolls|Magic detection]]\n[[Category:Hack'EM scrolls|Magic detection]]"}